TC) that is responsible for coordinating all distributed transactions started locally, and the default time after which a transaction times out. In addition, it specifies a setting that can only be modified at the machine level, which is the maximum amount of time allowed before a transaction times out.\"\n  version:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  - xamarinmac-3.0\n  monikers:\n  - netframework-4.5.1\n  - netframework-4.5.2\n  - netframework-4.5\n  - netframework-4.6.1\n  - netframework-4.6.2\n  - netframework-4.6\n  - netframework-4.7\n  - xamarinmac-3.0\n  content_git_url: https://github.com/dotnet/docs/blob/master/xml/ns-System.Transactions.Configuration.xml\n  ms.technology:\n  - dotnet-standard\n  manager: ghogen\nreferences:\n- uid: System.Transactions.Configuration.DefaultSettingsSection\n  parent: System.Transactions.Configuration\n  isExternal: false\n  name: DefaultSettingsSection\n  nameWithType: DefaultSettingsSection\n  fullName: System.Transactions.Configuration.DefaultSettingsSection\n- uid: System.Transactions.Configuration.MachineSettingsSection\n  parent: System.Transactions.Configuration\n  isExternal: false\n  name: MachineSettingsSection\n  nameWithType: MachineSettingsSection\n  fullName: System.Transactions.Configuration.MachineSettingsSection\n- uid: System.Transactions.Configuration.TransactionsSectionGroup\n  parent: System.Transactions.Configuration\n  isExternal: false\n  name: TransactionsSectionGroup\n  nameWithType: TransactionsSectionGroup\n  fullName: System.Transactions.Configuration.TransactionsSectionGroup\n"}